This directory contains application assets loaded by the WebView.

License classification by file:
  - chess.html: Combined work (AGPL v3 + GPL v3)
      Built from chess.src/ modules by build-chess.py / build-chess.sh.
      The HTML/CSS template is AGPL v3; the embedded JavaScript modules
      include GPL v3 (DroidFish-derived) and AGPL v3 (original) code.
      See chess.src/README.license for per-module details.
  - stats.html: GPL v3 (PGN parsing derived from DroidFish)
      Fullscreen statistics page (📊统计). Contains time-management analysis,
      clickable variation moves, FEN panel, FEN-embedded PGN support,
      static HTML export dialog with GPL v3 notice. PGN parsing logic
      derived from DroidFish GameTree/PgnToken/PgnScanner (GPL v3).
  - AGPLv3_Logo.svg: FSF official AGPL v3 logo
      Used for license identification on the About page.
      Source: https://www.gnu.org/graphics/agplv3-with-text-162x68.png
  - GPLv3_Logo.svg: FSF official GPL v3 logo
      Used for license identification on the 💾HTML export dialog.
      Source: https://www.gnu.org/graphics/gplv3-127x51.png
  - chess.src/: Source modules (see chess.src/README.license)

v1.0.2 changes reflected in chess.html (rebuilt from chess.src/):
  - ECO opening auto-fill: when a new game starts with a selected ECO
    opening whose `moves` array contains full move data, the moves are
    auto-filled into moveRecords with proper SAN notation — no "..."
    placeholder is needed even when the opening's last move was Black's.
  - Black-to-move opening placeholder: for FEN/setup/PGN imports with
    Black to move (no ECO moves), a null placeholder is prepended to
    moveRecords so Black's first move lands in the Black slot.
  - PGN export evaluation annotations: _buildPGNString() now appends
    `{score eval_word}` after every move with a cached eval, and
    `{SF18 D22 +1.0 8%W/91%D/1%L}` every 5 moves (engine name, depth,
    score, WDL).
  - "Play Again" button now shows ⚔️ prefix (consistent with the
    New Game button).
  - Redo no longer triggers AI (prevents redo-stack corruption).
  - Settings import via file picker no longer shows a duplicate toast
    (the onSettingsImported callback is the single source of truth).

See the root-level LICENSE-AGPL v3, LICENSE-GPL v3, and NOTICE files
for full license texts and attribution details.

v1.0.2 NEW FEATURE additions:
  - stats.html: GPL v3 (PGN parsing derived from DroidFish)
      Fullscreen statistics page opened by the 📊统计 button. Renders the
      current game's PGN with rich formatting (piece symbols, comments,
      variations) and computes statistics (material balance, eval trend,
      move quality classification, accuracy).
      PGN parsing logic (parsePGN function) is derived from DroidFish
      GameTree/PgnToken/PgnScanner (Copyright (C) Peter Österlund, GPL v3).
      Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      License: GPL v3 (to match the DroidFish-derived PGN parsing code).
      v1.0.2 updates:
        - parsePGN() now prefers _payload.moveRecords (authoritative move
          list from the main app) over re-parsing the PGN string. The
          simplified SAN parser's cascade-failure bug capped total moves
          at ~98; using the authoritative move list fixes this.
        - renderPGNText() piece symbols now use the same color/stroke/glow
          as the main board (wrapped in <span class="piece-white/black">
          with higher CSS specificity than .pgn-display .move).
        - 📂 Select PGN File opens SAF picker directly from StatsActivity
          (no longer bounces through MainActivity).

v1.0.3 changes (reflected in stats.html and rebuilt chess.html):
  - stats.html: NEW time-management analysis feature.
      extractMoveTimes(pgnText) parses per-move thinking times from PGN
      comments. Two conventions are supported:
        1. v1.0.3 direct format: `{3.2s +0.5 略优}` (time + space + eval).
           No header needed; the `<number>s` pattern is the move's used time.
        2. Standard PGN clock format (requires [TimeControl] header):
           `[%clk HH:MM:SS]` gives the player's REMAINING clock after the
           move. The app parses `[TimeControl "BASE+INC"]` to get the base
           time and per-move increment, tracks each player's previous
           remaining clock (initialized to baseTime), and derives used time
           via `used = previousClock + increment - currentClk`. Three
           TimeControl notations are supported: "7200+60" (base+increment),
           "1800" (base only), "40/7200" (moves-per-time, treated as no
           increment). Without a [TimeControl] header, [%clk] values are
           recorded as clock-remaining only — not used to derive used time.
           If a move has both a {N.Ns} direct comment and a [%clk], the
           direct format takes precedence.
      Also recognizes the earlier em-dash format `{<sec>s——...}` for
      backward compatibility, and standard `[%clk HH:MM:SS]`.
      The Time Management section shows: total/White/Black time used,
      average per move, slowest/fastest move (with move number), time
      volatility (standard deviation), long-think count (>10s), quick-move
      count (<1s), phase distribution (opening/midgame/endgame), and an
      SVG bar chart of per-move thinking time. When a [TimeControl] header
      is present, a blue info bar at the top lists the base time and
      per-move increment.
  - stats.html: NEW clickable variation moves.
      Previously only mainline moves were clickable for per-position
      statistics. In v1.0.3, variation moves inside `(...)` are also
      clickable. On click, selectVariationMove(varId, varMoveIdx) builds
      a synthetic move sequence: mainline[0..mainIdxBefore-1] + ALL
      variation moves[0..varClickedIdx] (the ENTIRE series from the
      variation's first move to the clicked move, not just the clicked
      move). mainIdxBefore is the index of the mainline move that the
      variation's first move REPLACES (the move immediately to the LEFT
      of `(`). The synthetic sequence is then used for ALL stats
      computation. Variation moves from index 0 to varClickedIdx are
      visually highlighted (class "var-included" for moves before the
      clicked one, "selected" for the clicked one) to communicate that
      the entire series is being used.
  - stats.html: Variation text rendered in italic.
      The `.pgn-display .variation` CSS rule now includes `font-style:italic`
      so the `()` parentheses and all content inside are visually distinct
      from mainline moves.
  - stats.html: NEW FEN panel below the PGN text panel.
      renderFENPanel() generates a FEN string from the selected move's
      post-state via stateToFEN(state). The panel shows the FEN of the
      position right after the selected move (mainline or variation),
      with a copy-to-clipboard button. If no move is selected, shows the
      initial position FEN + a hint.
  - stats.html: NEW selection banner.
      A small banner above the PGN text panel shows the currently selected
      move number (mainline or variation), making it clear which position
      the stats below correspond to. For variation selections, the banner
      shows the RANGE of variation moves (1 to N) and the total count,
      explicitly noting that the entire series replaces the single
      mainline move.
  - stats.html: v1.0.3 FIX — clear stale moveRecords on PGN import.
      When a new PGN is imported (via _statsPastePGN or onStatsPGNFileRead),
      _payload.moveRecords and _payload.evals are now cleared to null.
      Without this clear, parsePGN() would detect the stale moveRecords
      from the PREVIOUS game and call parseFromMoveRecords() — replaying
      the old game's moves instead of parsing the newly imported PGN text.
      This was the root cause of "imported PGN not recognized": the
      metadata (headers) was extracted from the new PGN (correct) but the
      moves/positions came from the old game's moveRecords (wrong), and
      [%clk]/[TimeControl] time analysis showed the right times but for
      the wrong number of moves. Also clears _variationMoves and
      _variationMeta to reset the variation-selection state.
  - stats.html: Bilingual UI strings added for all new features (fen_label,
      fen_hint, fen_copy, time_*, time_control_header, time_base_time,
      time_increment, variation_marker, select_hint, select_var_hint, etc.)
      — supports the existing ↔️ Chinese/English language toggle.
  - chess.src/ai-bridge.js: _buildPGNComment() format uses a single space
      as separator between thinking time and eval annotation.
      Examples:
        "{3.2s +0.5 略优}"   (time + short eval)
        "{3.2s SF18 D22 +1.0 8%W/91%D/1%L}"  (time + full SF18 line)
        "{3.2s}"             (time only — no trailing space)
        "{+0.5 略优}"         (eval only — no separator)
  - chess.src/ui.js, game-logic.js, index.html.tpl: version strings
    updated from v1.0.2 → v1.0.3 (header badge, about dialog, loading
    title, built_in_only string, <title>).

v1.0.3 patch changes (version number unchanged — still v1.0.3 / versionCode 103):
  - chess.html (rebuilt from chess.src/):
      * PGN import: Type A variations (alternatives to the owning move)
        are no longer incorrectly relocated to the next move. App-exported
        PGNs with variations now round-trip correctly on re-import.
      * PGN import: embedded [FEN] header support — the FEN's
        fullMoveNumber is used as the starting move number for the move
        list, review mode, and PGN export.
      * Landscape review layout: removed the max-width cap on .review-moves
        so the move list takes all remaining horizontal space (was capped
        to board_width - 8px, wasting hundreds of pixels on tablets/wide
        screens). Also removed the 360px hard cap on board width.
  - No changes to stats.html in this patch.
  - No changes to AGPLv3_Logo.svg or GPLv3_Logo.svg.
